RADIUS Attributes for IPv6 Access
Networks
2013", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="This document specifies additional IPv6 RADIUS Attributes useful in residential broadband network deployments.  The Attributes, which are used for authorization and accounting, enable assignment of a host IPv6 address and an IPv6 DNS server address via DHCPv6, assignment of an IPv6 route announced via router advertisement, assignment of a named IPv6 delegated prefix pool, and assignment of a named IPv6 pool for host DHCPv6 addressing.", style=filled, fillcolor=green]; 

